gomodel:SYNGO_4002  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7, A and B: Fluorescence microscopy targeted towards intracellular and total GluA2 was used to calculate the GluA2 internalisation index. TSPAN7 Knockdown demonstrated an increase in the GluA2 internalisation index indicating its role as a regulator in GluA2 trafficking in the post-synapse. To ascertain that the effect was a true representation of endocytosis of GluA2 receptor, a similar experiment in the presence of dynamin inhibitor Dynasore was carried out. Dynasore abolished the differences in the internalization index between TSPAN7-knockdown and scrambled siRNA14 neurons.\nFigure 8 A: Rescue WT rescues the effect of TSPAN7 knockdown by reducing the internalization index close to control levels. Overexpression of TSPAN7 reduces the GluA2 internalization index compared to control.. Experimental description: Rat embryos (gestation age 18d) were used to culture hippocampal neurons for the experiments and were derived from Charles River, Italy." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4002" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

